(
<figureCitation box="[273,406,1455,1481]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 16–21" captionStart-1="FIGURES 22–24" captionStart-2="FIGURES 25–28" captionStart-3="FIGURES 29–31" captionStart-4="FIGURE 32" captionStartId-0="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionStartId-1="8.[264,382,1806,1830]" captionStartId-2="9.[264,383,1841,1865]" captionStartId-3="11.[264,383,1595,1619]" captionStartId-4="12.[264,368,1409,1433]" captionTargetBox-0="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetBox-1="[362,1285,494,1796]" captionTargetBox-2="[368,1176,734,1828]" captionTargetBox-3="[321,1245,324,1564]" captionTargetBox-4="[264,1313,449,1384]" captionTargetId-0="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetId-1="figure-100@8.[295,1292,470,1801]" captionTargetId-2="figure-176@9.[291,1280,704,1842]" captionTargetId-3="figure-66@11.[299,1289,306,1592]" captionTargetId-4="figure-141@12.[66,1313,449,1384]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionTargetPageId-2="9" captionTargetPageId-3="11" captionTargetPageId-4="12" captionText-0="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." captionText-1="FIGURES 22–24. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 22. Female midtarsal claw and empodium (lateral). 23. Male abdominal segment 5 to end (dorsolateral). 24. Female abdominal segment 6 to end (dorsolateral)." captionText-2="FIGURES 25–28. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 25. Male terminalia (dorsal). 26. Female tergite 8 and ovipositor. 27. Pupal head (frontal). 28. Pupal prothoracic spiracle." captionText-3="FIGURES 29–31. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 29. Pupal terminal segments (dorsal). 30. Larval spatula and associated papillae. 31. Larval terminal segments." captionText-4="FIGURE 32. Galls of Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. on Bauhinia brevipes." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" figureD