<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,1534,1881]" lastBlockId="7.[264,1321,284,350]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,343,1534,1560]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Adult.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[519,664,1535,1561]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="2.05" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.8">1.8–2.3 mm</quantity>
in male (
<emphasis box="[784,799,1535,1560]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">n</emphasis>
= 5); 
<quantity box="[879,1037,1535,1561]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.425" metricValueMax="2.45" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="2.425" valueMax="2.45" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.45 mm</quantity>
in female (
<emphasis box="[1181,1196,1535,1560]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">n</emphasis>
= 2, from vertex to posterior margin of tergite 8). Head (
<figureCitation box="[809,953,1575,1601]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Figs. 16, 17</figureCitation>
): Eye facets hexagonal, closely appressed. Antenna with scape cylindrical, elongate, setose, pedicel globose, setose, male and female flagellomeres cylindrical, flagellomere necks short and bare. Male flagellomeres 9–12 subequal in length (
<figureCitation box="[732,820,1695,1721]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); female flagellomeres 9–12 progressively and conspicuously shortened (
<figureCitation box="[633,724,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Flagellomeres 1 and 2 not connate. Circumfila sinuous in male (
<figureCitation box="[468,555,1775,1801]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) and linear in female (
<figureCitation box="[827,916,1775,1801]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Frontoclypeus with 14–16 setae. Labrum long­attenuate with 2 pairs of ventral sensory setae. Hypopharynx of same shape as labrum, with long, anteriorly directed lateral setulae. Labella hemispherical, each with several lateral setae and 2 pairs of short mesal sensory setae. Palpus with 4 setose segments: first segment globose, others cylindrical.
</paragraph>
