<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1324,284,430]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Thorax: Anepimeron setose, other pleural sclerites asetose. Wing length (from arculus to apex): 
<quantity box="[375,544,324,350]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.525" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.45" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.525" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.45">1.45–1.60 mm</quantity>
in male (
<emphasis box="[656,671,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">n</emphasis>
= 5); 
<quantity box="[741,831,324,350]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
in female (
<emphasis box="[964,979,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">n</emphasis>
= 2). First tarsomere without apical spur. Tarsal claws simple, bent beyond midlength; empodia well developed, as long as bend in claws (
<figureCitation box="[473,561,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–24" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1806,1830]" captionTargetBox="[362,1285,494,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[295,1292,470,1801]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22–24. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 22. Female midtarsal claw and empodium (lateral). 23. Male abdominal segment 5 to end (dorsolateral). 24. Female abdominal segment 6 to end (dorsolateral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051093/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
