<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1324,284,670]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">
Abdomen. Male (
<figureCitation box="[527,620,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–24" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1806,1830]" captionTargetBox="[362,1285,494,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[295,1292,470,1801]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22–24. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 22. Female midtarsal claw and empodium (lateral). 23. Male abdominal segment 5 to end (dorsolateral). 24. Female abdominal segment 6 to end (dorsolateral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051093/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
): tergites 1–7 rectangular with complete row of posterior setae, several lateral setae, 2 basal trichoid sensilla and elsewhere with scattered scales. Tergite 8 linear with only 2 trichoid sensilla as vestiture. Sternites 2–7 rectangular with setae more abundant at midlength, complete row of posterior setae and 2 basal trichoid sensilla; sternite 8 ovoid with several scattered setae and 2 basal trichoid sensilla. Female (
<figureCitation box="[273,368,484,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–24" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1806,1830]" captionTargetBox="[362,1285,494,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[295,1292,470,1801]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22–24. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 22. Female midtarsal claw and empodium (lateral). 23. Male abdominal segment 5 to end (dorsolateral). 24. Female abdominal segment 6 to end (dorsolateral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051093/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
): tergites 1–6 as in male; tergite 7 rectangular with setae more abundant at midlength, complete row of posterior setae and 2 basal trichoid sensilla; tergite 8 notched laterally with only 2 basal trichoid sensilla as vestiture. Sternites 2–6 as in male. Sternite 7 much longer than preceding sternite, with rounded margins, scattered setae and 2 basal trichoid sensilla. Sternite 8 not sclerotized.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051097" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5051097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051097/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="36" startId="9.[264,383,1841,1865]" targetBox="[368,1176,734,1828]" targetPageId="9">
