<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,452,1444,1470]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2005" box="[584,762,1444,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocapillata">
<emphasis box="[584,762,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">macrocapillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed of 
<emphasis box="[954,1039,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">makros</emphasis>
(long) + 
<emphasis box="[1150,1243,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">capillus</emphasis>
(hair), and refers to the presence of the long hairs on the gall surface.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,433,1524,1550]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2005" box="[443,765,1524,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocapillata">
<emphasis box="[443,765,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Schizomyia macrocapillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1189,1322,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Schizomyia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, mainly due to the presence of a distinct female cercus. Additionally, male tergite 8 is linear and asetose with two trichoid sensilla, the ovipositor is 
<quantity box="[1012,1101,1604,1630]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long, the larva has setose sternal papillae, and the pupa has the antennal base thickened. Previous studies on these galls identified the gall­inducing insect as 
<taxonomicName box="[864,992,1684,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Contarinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[864,992,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Contarinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fernandes G. W. &amp; Price P. W." box="[1013,1318,1684,1710]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="14 - 20" refId="ref3821" refString="Fernandes G. W. &amp; Price P. W. (1992) The adaptive significance of insect gall distribution: survivorship of species in xeric and mesic habitats. Oecologia, 90, 14 - 20." type="journal article" year="1992">Fernandes &amp; Price 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cornelissen T. G. &amp; Madeira, B. G. &amp; Allain, L. R. &amp; Lara, A. C. F. &amp; Araujo, L. M. &amp; Fernandes, G. W." box="[264,575,1724,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="285 - 288" refId="ref3534" refString="Cornelissen T. G., Madeira, B. G., Allain, L. R., Lara, A. C. F., Araujo, L. M., Fernandes, G. W. (1997) Multiple responses of insect herbivores to plant vigor. Ciencia &amp; Cultura, 49, 285 - 288." type="journal article" year="1997">
Cornelissen 
<emphasis box="[422,494,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">et al.</emphasis>
1997
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cornelissen T. G. &amp; Negreiros, D. &amp; Fernandes, G. W." box="[600,662,1724,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="135 - 150" refId="ref3598" refString="Cornelissen T. G., Negreiros, D. &amp; Fernandes, G. W. (2002) Plant resistance against gall-forming insects: the role of hypersensitivity. In: Wagner, M. (Ed.), Mechanisms and Deployment of Resistance in Trees to Insects. Kluwer Academic Press, pp. 135 - 150." type="book chapter" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fernandes G. W. &amp; Cornelissen, T. G." box="[687,1091,1724,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="144 - 152" refId="ref3739" refString="Fernandes G. W. &amp; Cornelissen, T. G. (1997) Plant hypersensitivity against tissue invasive insects: Bauhinia brevipes and Contarinia sp. interaction. In: Czoka, Y., Price, P. W., Mattson, W. J. (Eds.), The Biology of Gall Arthropods. United States Department of Agriculture, General Technical Report NC- 199, North Carolina, pp. 144 - 152." type="book chapter" year="1997">Fernandes &amp; Cornelissen 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fernandes G. W." box="[1116,1318,1724,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="260 - 267" refId="ref3704" refString="Fernandes G. W. 1998. Hypersensitivity as a phenotypic basis of plant induced resistance against a galling insect (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae). Environmental Entomology, 27, 260 - 267." type="journal article" year="1998">Fernandes 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cornelissen T. G. &amp; Fernandes, G. W." box="[264,669,1764,1790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="236 - 241" refId="ref3402" refString="Cornelissen T. G. &amp; Fernandes, G. W. (2001 a) Induced defenses in the neotropical tree Bauhinia brevipes to herbivory: effects of damage-induced changes on leaf quality and insect herbivore attack. Trees, 15, 236 - 241." type="journal article" year="2001">Cornelissen &amp; Fernandes, 2001a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cornelissen T. &amp; Fernandes, G. W." box="[688,763,1764,1790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="246 - 253" refId="ref3449" refString="Cornelissen T. G &amp; Fernandes, G. W. (2001 b) Defense, growth, and nutrient allocation in the tropical shrub Bauhinia brevipes (Leguminosae). Austral Ecology, 246 - 253." type="book chapter" year="2001">2001b</bibRefCitation>
, 2000c; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fernandes G. W. &amp; Cornelissen, T. G. &amp; Isaias, R. M. S. &amp; Lara, A. F." box="[876,1151,1764,1790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="49 - 54" refId="ref3860" refString="Fernandes G. W., Cornelissen, T. G., Isaias, R. M. S. &amp; Lara, A. F. (2000) Plants fight gall formation: hypersensitivity. Ciencia e Cultura, 52, 49 - 54." type="journal article" year="2000">
Fernandes 
<emphasis box="[1009,1067,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
), probably an inquiline.
</paragraph>
